Gang Events Hosting SOP
Important Commands
General Event Commands
:eventmsg


→ To send out mass event message

:gevents


→ To warp to gang events level

:settings


→ For GUI

/fixsales


→ To fix the R scoreboard if it breaks

MVP & Gang Award Commands
Preparation (Required Before Awarding)
/gat


→ Add the gang award tool to the account before any of the following

MVP Winner Command
:mvpwinner account 1

Individual Gang Coin
:gcwinner Account 1

Award Entire Gang
:awardgang “gang name” #


→ Need ETA rights
→ Awards Gang Coins

Force Gang Tags
:gangtags

:tb


→ For Ballas

:tbl


→ For Temnaya

Hosting Gang Events
Event 1 — Simulation Raid (Sim Raid)
Location & Maps

Head to:

era_ow-inside-eventhouse-gangevents.nw


Go into:

Simulation Raid Event
era_simulation-raid_00-00.nw


New Map:

era_ow-gangevent-simraid-midnight_01-01.nw

Hosting Steps

Type:

:reset points


→ Reset scoreboard

Type:

/host


→ Search for Simulation Raid and send it.

Leaderboard Monitoring & Rewards
Keep an eye out on '3' for leaderboard.

Award as Following:
Sim Raid

Top 3 players - 1 mvp coin 

1st place  - 4 gang coins
2nd place  - 3 gang coins
3rd place  - 2 gang coin
4th place  - 1 gang coin

During :gevents Events
:cleargame

Event 2 — King of the Hill (KoTH)
Setup Steps

While in ET tag, type:

:gevents


Type in:

:ep
:bb
:bh
:lc
:ch


→ Whichever ones made it to the top 4

Type:

:settings


→ Choose KoTH - Main

Once each gang has been situated by player count:

:start

Leaderboard & Rewards
Keep an eye out for the leaderboards.

Award as Following:
1st place - 1 mvp to each player
2nd place - 2 gang coins
3rd place - 1 gang coins 

(if doing 4 gangs, award 2nd place 3, 3rd place 2, and 4th place 1)

Event 3 — 1v1 Gang Events

You can choose between:

TDM

CTF

Kill Confirmed

Payload

TTS

Team Spar

Poll in Discord if desired.

Setup Instructions

These are 1v1 Gang events, so select the two who will face each other.

Kick the rest if needed.

Example for CTF

Type:

:settings


Select:

CTF - Whiteout


New map as of 10/13/24:

Blitz


Much more streamlined

Better respawning mechanics

Host this one when possible

Type:

:start


→ When ready

Important Notes

Winners will remain after finish.

Do not award until the winner has been selected.

Payload Rounds Explanation

Payload rounds work on a:

“Which gang can get the payload further” type system.


Suggestions:

5 minute rounds to keep things moving

Give each gang a chance at attacker and defender

Whichever gets further takes the round

Example 3 Gang Bracket for 1v1 Events

(Bracket example remains as originally intended)

Rewards
Same reward structure as KoTH

Final Event — Gang Wars

Unless you want to finish with Team Spar, TTS, or another sparring event.

Location

Move to:

era_event-gangwars-lobby.nw

Entry Path

Head to:

era_ow-inside-eventhouse-gangevents.nw


Go through the Gang Wars door.

Gathering Participants

Collect all the gangs that have been competing.

The list on the level will identify who is playing.

Previous method observed:

Amber would obtain the gang leader.

Have them PM names of who to use.

Suggested logical method:

Identify member limit first.

Have them PM us the number of members.

Include themselves in this count.

Starting Gang Wars

Type:

:start


Begin adding all the members to each gang.

Important Commands During Gang Wars
:add         → Add member
:remove      → Remove member
:get         → Participant list as PM
:reset       → Reset everything
:next        → Next gangs
:display     → Updates display
:in          → Warp in fighter
:winner      → Add to winner list
:delwinner   → Remove from winner list
:nextround   → When every member is winner
:addall      → Add every ontag member
:sa          → Summon all participants
:gangtags    → Set gangtags on everyone in the level

Running the Rounds

Once all gang members have been added:

:timer


→ Begin selection process

Warp both members:

:in


The winner will be PM'd to you via NPCServer.

Can copy+paste winner command.

Keep doing steps 5–7 until the round is complete.

If odd:

:winner


the individual remaining

Type:

:nextround


→ Move winners back to the beginning

Repeat steps 5–10 until:

Last gang standing

Or last winner standing

Special Case

If multiple of the same gang members are still standing:

Run them through the spar.

Rewards for Gang Wars
1st place - 2 mvp coins to each player 
            + 1 mvp for overall mvp sparrer

2nd place - 2 gang coins
3rd place - 1 gang coin

(if doing 4 gangs, award 2nd place 3, 3rd place 2, and 4th place 1)

Final Step

Award the final winner.

Gang Events Complete
After Event Cleanup

Reset weekly count in RC:

/npcresetpoints


(Currently not authorized)

Run:

:farena 3600


→ 60 minute runtime

Invoke Double points as well.

Needs to be manually turned off.
